@NODE Introduction "ToyJoin - Introduction"

  @{b}Introduction@{ub}

  ToyJoin is a complete replacement to DayDream's "join conference"-commands.
  It was programmed with ASM-One v1.29 by T.F.A.

  @{b}Features@{ub}

  o Free (email-ware).
  o Small size (6000 bytes).
  o Quite fast.
  o Residentable.
  o Very configurable. DayDream-like text based config.
  o Every node, displaymode and accesslevel can have their own configs.
  o Can hide /Ācolor differently confs which the user hasn't access to.
  o You may define certain confs which will always be hide.
  o Able to relatively number the conferences.
  o You can define so-called infolines for each conference.
  o Fast prompt joining.
  o Cursor key conference selecting.
  o Hot-looking ANSI-graphics & example configs included.
  o With add-on door called ToySince, you are able to display user's
    uploads since last call in the menu.
  o With add-on utility called ToyDay, you are able to display today's
    uploads in the menu.

  @{b}Requirements@{ub}

  o Running DayDream BBS.
  o Dreamdoor.library v5 or higher.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "ToyJoin - Installation"

  @{b}Installation@{ub}

  Copy the "Configs", "Doors", "Display" and "Utils" directories to your
  DayDream directory. Install ToyJoin as a normal DayDream BBS door.
  You may test it with the $ command before installing it.

DOOR_COMMAND.. J
DOOR_TYPE..... 1
DOOR_SECURITY. 200                               ;Change this to suit you.
DOOR_EXECUTE.. Doors:ToyJoin %N
DOOR_CONFS1... XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
DOOR_CONFS2... XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
+
DOOR_COMMAND.. <
DOOR_TYPE..... 1
DOOR_SECURITY. 200                               ;Change this to suit you.
DOOR_EXECUTE.. Doors:ToyJoin %N
DOOR_CONFS1... XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
DOOR_CONFS2... XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
+
DOOR_COMMAND.. >
DOOR_TYPE..... 1
DOOR_SECURITY. 200                               ;Change this to suit you.
DOOR_EXECUTE.. Doors:ToyJoin %N
DOOR_CONFS1... XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
DOOR_CONFS2... XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

@ENDNODE

@NODE Configuration "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  @{b}Environment Variable@{ub}

  ToyJoin has an optional enviroment variable called "ToyJoin". It can be
  used to speed up prompt joining. The variable contains 4 characters which
  are either "Y" or "N". Make a file to ENVARC: or use the SetENV command.

  SetENV ToyJoin NYNY
                 ||||
                 |||`--- Enable conference cycling. [CYCLE CONFERENCES]
                 ||`--- Display menu if no access. [SKIP_NOACCESS]
                 |`--- Skip joingfx when prompt joining. [SKIP_JOINGRAPHICS]
                 `--- Use relative conference numbering. [RELATIVE_CONFS]

  Actually you barely notice the minimal speed change on remote connections
  but it's a little bit faster when using local. :)


  @{b}Background Display@{ub}

  ToyJoin doesn't display any hardcoded copyright texts or childish
  elite-cased banners but @{i}please credit me somewhere in the menu@{ui}!

  The name of the background display is controlled with the @{" BACKGROUND_FILE " LINK BACKGROUND_FILE}
  option in ToyJoin's configuration file.

  Put the display files in your displaymode directories. You can also have
  own displays for certain conferences.

  You can use DayDream's @{" special control codes " LINK DayDream:Docs/DayDream.guide/BBS11} to create random displays,
  display the user's name, local time etc.

  You can also create own displays for different security levels.
  Eg. "ToyJoin.210.GFX" for security level 210.


  @{b}Configuration Files@{ub}

  Put your configuration file(s) to your DayDream config directory which
  usually is "DayDream:Configs".

  You can have own config files for certain display modes, access levels
  and even nodes. You could for example create own configs for telnet users
  and own for normal remote users.

  If there are no special configs for the user, the normal "ToyJoin.CFG"
  will be loaded.

  The filename format is:

     ToyJoin.nX.dmY.axZ.CFG
             |   |   |
             |   |   `--- Access level (001-255)
             |   `--- Display mode (1-254)
             `--- Node (1-254)

  Some examples:

     ToyJoin.n1.dm3.ax210.CFG   (node 1, displaymode 3, access 210)
     ToyJoin.n4.dm1.CFG         (node 4, displaymode 1)
     ToyJoin.ax050.CFG          (access 50)
     ToyJoin.CFG                (normal configuration)


  @{b}Configuration Options@{ub}

     @{" HIDE ALWAYS " LINK HIDE_ALWAYS}

     @{" RELATIVE_CONFS " LINK RELATIVE_CONFS}

     @{" USE_TWO_ROWS " LINK USE_TWO_ROWS}
     @{" HIDE_NOACCESS " LINK HIDE_NOACCESS}
     @{" USE_HOTKEYS " LINK USE_HOTKEYS}

     @{" USE_CUSTOMNAMES " LINK USE_CUSTOMNAMES}
     @{" USE_INFOLINES " LINK USE_INFOLINES}

     @{" SKIP_JOINGRAPHICS " LINK SKIP_JOINGRAPHICS}
     @{" SKIP_NOACCESS " LINK SKIP_NOACCESS}
     @{" CYCLE_CONFERENCES " LINK CYCLE_CONFERENCES}

     @{" MENU_TIMEOUT " LINK MENU_TIMEOUT}

     @{" ROW1_X_COORDINATE " LINK COORDINATES}
     @{" ROW1_Y_COORDINATE " LINK COORDINATES}
     @{" ROW2_X_COORDINATE " LINK COORDINATES}
     @{" ROW2_Y_COORDINATE " LINK COORDINATES}

     @{" MENUROW_ACCESS " LINK MENUROWS}
     @{" MENUROW_NOACCESS " LINK MENUROWS}
     @{" SELECTOR_ACCESS " LINK SELECTORS}
     @{" SELECTOR_NOACCESS " LINK SELECTORS}

     @{" COMMANDROW_STRING " LINK COMMANDROW_STRING}
     @{" INFOROW_STRING " LINK INFOROW_STRING}
     @{" CURSOR_STRING " LINK CURSOR_STRING}

     @{" BACKGROUND_FILE " LINK BACKGROUND_FILE}
     @{" CONFNAMES_FILE " LINK CONFNAMES_FILE}
     @{" INFOLINES_FILE " LINK INFOLINES_FILE}


  @{b}Prompthelp Display@{ub}

  If you give a "?" parameter to any prompt command, ToyJoin displays
  "ToyJoin_PromptHelp" from the displaymode directory.


  @{b}Menuhelp Display@{ub}

  If you press [help] or [h] in the menu, ToyJoin displays "ToyJoin_MenuHelp"
  from the displaymode directory.


  @{b}Confhelp Display@{ub}

  If you press [i] in the menu, ToyJoin displays "ToyJoin_ConfHelp" from
  the displaymode directory. Use this for conference info or whatever.

@ENDNODE

@NODE HIDE_ALWAYS "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  HIDE_ALWAYS........ <LIST>

  This is a list of conferences which will be hide from the users.
  These conferences can be joined only from command prompt and they won't
  be seen in the menu.

  Example:

  HIDE_ALWAYS........ 1,15,16

@ENDNODE

@NODE RELATIVE_CONFS "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  RELATIVE_CONFS..... [Y/N]

  This option enables relative conference numbering, affects both prompt
  and menu. For example if your conf access is "__XX___..." (you have
  access to confs 3 and 4), you would have to use "J 3" or "J 4" to join
  them directly. If RELATIVE_CONFS is enabled, you could use "J 1" and "J 2".
  This also affects the numbering in the menu. Good especially if you have
  some confs hided from certain users.

@ENDNODE

@NODE USE_TWO_ROWS "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  USE_TWO_ROWS....... [Y/N]

  If you set USE_TWO_ROWS to Y, ToyJoin will create two rows in the menu.
  The coordinates of these rows can be controlled with the coordinate
  options.

@ENDNODE

@NODE HIDE_NOACCESS "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  HIDE_NOACCESS...... [Y/N]

  If HIDE_NOACCESS is Y, all conferences which the user has no access to,
  will be hided (not displayed in the menu at all).

  Check out @{" RELATIVE CONFS " LINK RELATIVE_CONFS}.
   
@ENDNODE

@NODE USE_HOTKEYS "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  USE_HOTKEYS........ [Y/N]

  If you enable hotkeys, you don't need to press enter when using
  the menu and entering the conference number directly.

@ENDNODE

@NODE USE_CUSTOMNAMES "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  USE_CUSTOMNAMES.... [Y/N]

  If you want to use custom names for certain conferences, enable this.

  Check out @{" CONFNAMES_FILE " LINK CONFNAMES_FILE}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE USE_INFOLINES "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  USE_INFOLINES...... [Y/N]

  This option enables so-called infolines which give some info about the
  current conference under the menu selector.

  Check out @{" INFOROW_STRING " LINK INFOROW_STRING} and @{" INFOLINES_FILE " LINK INFOLINES_FILE}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE SKIP_JOINGRAPHICS "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  SKIP_JOINGRAPHICS.. [Y/N]

  If this option is Y, ToyJoin won't show JoinConference.GFX or TXT when using
  join commands from prompt. When joining conferences from the menu,
  graphics will always be shown.

  The idea behind this is that first time users on your board usually use
  the menu while old users prefer fast prompt usage.

@ENDNODE

@NODE SKIP_NOACCESS "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  SKIP_NOACCESS...... [Y/N]

  This option is for prompt usage only. If enabled, the menu will be shown
  instead of "You have noa access to that conference!" text.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CYCLE_CONFERENCES "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  CYCLE_CONFERENCES.. [Y/N]

  If enabled, users can cycle from the first to the last conf and vice versa
  with the "<" and ">" commands.

@ENDNODE

@NODE MENU_TIMEOUT "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  MENU_TIMEOUT....... [number/-]

  Quit the menu after N seconds of inactivity. Put a "-" here if you don't
  want timeout.

  Attention! If you notice strange bugging in your system after installing
  ToyJoin, try to disable this option! DreamDoor.library's FetchKey() used
  to bug like hell and I'm not sure if Hydra ever managed to fix it 100%.

@ENDNODE

@NODE COORDINATES "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  ROW1_X_COORDINATE.. [number]
  ROW1_Y_COORDINATE.. [number]
  ROW2_X_COORDINATE.. [number]
  ROW2_Y_COORDINATE.. [number]

  These contain the coordinates of the menu rows.

@ENDNODE

@NODE MENUROWS "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  MENUROW_ACCESS..... [ANSI-String]
  MENUROW_NOACCESS... [ANSI-String]

  With these options you control what the menurows should look like.

  MENUROW_ACCESS is for confs which the user has access to and
  MENUROW_NOACCESS to ones which he doesn't.

  Examples:

  MENUROW_ACCESS..... <ESC>[%ld;ldH %02.ld  %s 

  The first "<ESC>[%ld;%ldH" is for placing the string to right position.
  No need to change it.

  The "%02.ld" stands for the conf number and the "%s" stands for
  conference name. You can control the field width, justification etc.
  as in RawDoFmt(). The "%02.ld" must exist and must be before the
  "%s". Best that you don't change the "%02.ld" at all.

  MENUROW_ACCESS..... %02.ld  %-14.14s 

  The "%-14.14s" means that 14 characters of the conference names
  would be displayed and left-justificated.

  Use ANSI-commands to color the strings.

  Check out @{" USE_CUSTOMNAMES " LINK USE_CUSTOMNAMES} and @{" selectors " LINK SELECTORS}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE SELECTORS "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  SELECTOR_ACCESS.... [ANSI-String]
  SELECTOR_NOACCESS.. [ANSI-String]

  With these options you control what the selectors should look like.
  (In ToyJoin, the selector means the selector image that moves in the menu)

  Use exactly like the @{" menurows " LINK MENUROWS}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE COMMANDROW_STRING "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  COMMANDROW_STRING.. [ANSI-String]

  This is the string for the commandrow. Remember to use ANSI commands to
  put the string in right place.

  You can use ranges by putting two "%02.ld"'s in this string.

  Example:

  COMMANDROW_STRING.. <ESC>[22;23HSelect Conference (%02.ld-%02.ld):

@ENDNODE

@NODE INFOROW_STRING "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  INFOROW_STRING..... [ANSI-String]

  This string is for the infoline placement.

  Example:

  INFOROW_STRING..... <ESC>[19;11H<ESC>[K<ESC>%s

@ENDNODE

@NODE CURSOR_STRING "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  CURSOR_STRING...... [ANSI-String]

  This is string is for the cursor placement and conference number.

  Example:

CURSOR_STRING...... <ESC>[22;56H%02.ld

  "%02.ld" stands for the conference number.

@ENDNODE

@NODE BACKGROUND_FILE "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  BACKGROUND_FILE.... [FILENAME]

  This is the plain filename (eg. "ToyJoin") for the background display.
  It will be seached from the displaymode directories and ".GFX" or ".TXT"
  will be added. You can also make own displays for certain access levels.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CONFNAMES_FILE "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  CONFNAMES_FILE..... [Filename]

  Full path and filename for custom conference names.

  Each line in the file is one name. Remember to put a linefeed after each
  name. You don't have to write own names for every conference! For example
  if the name for conference 2 is empty (just a linefeed), name for that
  conference will be taken from "Conferences.DAT". You can use ANSI commands
  in these names. 

  Example:

  CONFNAMES_FILE..... DayDream:Configs/ToyJoin.NAMES

  Check out @{" USE_CUSTOMNAMES " LINK USE_CUSTOMNAMES}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE INFOLINES_FILE "ToyJoin - Configuration"

  INFOLINES_FILE..... [Filename]

  Full path and filename for conference infolines. Each line is one infoline.
  ANSI commands can be used in these strings.

  Example:

  INFOLINES_FILE..... DayDream:Configs/ToyJoin.INFOS

@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "ToyJoin - Prompt & Menu Usage"

  @{b}Prompt Usage@{ub}

  Any prompt command followed by "?" displays prompt help.

  J [n]     Join conference [n].
  <         Join previous conference.
  < [n]     Jump [n] conferences backwards.
  <  0      Join the first conference.
  >         Join next conference.
  > [n]     Jump [n] conferences forwards.
  >  0      Join the last conference.


  @{b}Menu Usage@{ub}

  o Use cursor keys or numbers to move in the menu.
  o Pressing [enter] joins the conference under the selector. (if access)
  o Press [esc] (twice) or [q] to quit the menu.
  o Pressing [help] or [h] displays a help page.
  o Pressing [i] displays a conference info page.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Hints "ToyJoin - Hints"

  @{b}Add-Ons@{ub}

  In this package there are two add-ons included which can be used with
  ToyJoin or wherever. Check out the docs for these utils for more info.

     ToyDay     With this you can display today's uploaded bytes & files
                in the conference menu.

     ToySince   With this you can display bytes & files since lastcall
                in the conference menu or use it to create infolines.


  @{b}Infolines & ToySince@{ub}

  Nice way to configure your conference menu is that you create a config
  file for ToySince which contains @{" infolines " LINK USE_INFOLINES} for conferences and also
  ToySince keywords that output files/bytes since lastcall. Now when you
  move in the menu with cursor keys, you'll see the conference information
  plus amount of uploads since lastcall.

@ENDNODE

